Justina Asishana, Minna  The Acting Registrar of the National Examination Council (NECO), Abubakar Gana has said will not relent in discharging its responsibilities to conduct globally accepted examination. Just as he warned those in search of miracle centers to desist from examination malpractice to ensure a better Nigeria urging stakeholders in the education sector to salvage the sector from the dwindling fall in the standard of education. Speaking at the 1st annual celebration of the retirees of the non-academic staff union of educational and associated institutions (NASU), he said that their service in ensuring that the nation has one of the best examinations which is highly accepted will not be overlooked. He noted that the quality of well-being that employees enjoy is a reliable measure of the health of that company as a whole adding that NECO will never change in its welfare services to its staff. Gana further assured that NECO will continue to ensure the welfare of its retirees adding that this will ensure a better future for them and their household.